  "BuilderVersion": "0.1.18.1",
  "Hash": null,
  "SignedMessage": null,
  "LlmRequest": [
    {
      "temperature": 0.0,
      "top_p": 0.0,
      "frequencyPenalty": 0.0,
      "presencePenalty": 0.0,
      "maxLength": 4000,
      "llmResponseType": "json",
      "scheme": "{\"Reasoning\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Parameters\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter] = null, \"ReturnValues\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue] = null}\n\nAdditional information about objects:\nPLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Value\" : System.Object}\nPLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"VariableName\" : System.String}",
      "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
      "promptMessage": [
        {
          "role": "system",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "User is writing code in plang programming language.\r\n\r\nYour job is: \r\n1. Parse and understand user intent\r\n2. Map the intent to one of C# function provided to you\r\n3. Return a valid JSON\r\n\r\n## Rules\r\n%variable% in plang is defined with starting and ending percentage sign (%)\r\n%variable% MUST be wrapped in quotes(\") in json response, e.g. { \"name\":\"%name%\" }\r\nleave %variable% as is and do not change text to a variable\r\nnull is used to represent no value, e.g. { \"name\": null }\r\nVariables MUST not be changed, they can include dot(.) and parentheses()\r\nKeep \\n, \\r, \\t that are submitted to you for string variables\r\nParameters that is type System.String MUST be without escaping quotes. See <Example>\r\nError handling is process by another step, if you see 'on error...' you can ignore it\r\nIf there is some api key, settings, config replace it with %Settings.NameOfApiKey% \r\n- NameOfApiKey should named in relation to what is happening if change is needed\r\nDictionary<T1, T2> value is {key: value, ... } => a dictionary parameter defined as %variable% without key should have the same key and value as %variable%, e.g. %userId% => { key: \"userId\", value:\"%userId%\"}\r\nVariable with ToString with date/time formatting, assume it is System.DateTime, e.g. %updated.ToString(\"yyyy-MM-dd\")% then type of %updated% is System.DateTime \r\nList, ReadOnlyList are array of the object => e.g. user defines single property for List, return it as array\r\nWhen you see t%variable% or t\"this is text\", set the Type to Plang.TString. This is for translation\r\n<Example>\r\nget url \"http://example.org\" => Value: \"http://example.org\"\r\nwrite out 'Hello world' => Value: \"Hello world\"\r\n<Example>\r\n\r\n## JSON scheme information\r\nReasoning: A brief description of the reasoning behind the selection of the function and parameters based on the user's intent. This property provides context for why a particular function was chosen and how it aligns with the user intent.\r\nName: Name of the function to use from list of functions, if no function matches set as \"N/A\"\r\nParameters: List of parameters that are needed according to the user intent.\r\n- Type: the object type in c#\r\n- Name: name of the variable\r\n- Value: \"%variable%\", hardcode string that should be used, null, or json array/object\r\nReturnValue rules\r\n- Only if the function returns a value AND if user defines %variable% to write into, e.g. ' write into %data%' or 'into %result%', or simliar intent to write return value into variable\r\n- If no %variable% is defined then set as null."
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You MUST respond in JSON, scheme:\r\n {\"Reasoning\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Parameters\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter] = null, \"ReturnValues\" : System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue] = null}  Additional information about objects: PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+Parameter : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"Name\" : System.String, \"Value\" : System.Object} PLang.Modules.BaseBuilder+ReturnValue : {\"Type\" : System.String, \"VariableName\" : System.String}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "## Canonical User Intent (already disambiguated by LLM)\r\nAssign the value of the method property from the stepResult object to the MethodName property of the step object\n## functions available starts ##\r\n{\"Description\":\"Set, Get & Return variable(s). Set(NOT if statement) on variable includes condition such as empty or null. Bind onCreate, onChange, onRemove events to variable. Trim variable for llm. Use this module on `- return %variable`. Modify datetime (%now%, etc.)\",\"ExampleInformation\":\"Examples with methods first define an example plang code and then(=>) how it is mapped to parameters\",\"Methods\":[{\"MethodName\":\"Load\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"dataSourceName\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"},\"Examples\":[\"load %step% => variables=[\\\"%step%\\\"]\"]},{\"Description\":\"Loads(not setting a variable) a variable with a default value, key: variable name, value: default value. example: load %age%, default 10 => key:%age% value:10\",\"MethodName\":\"LoadWithDefaultValue\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"variablesWithDefaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"dataSourceName\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"},\"Examples\":[\"load %step%, set as 1 if empty => variablesWithDefaultValue=[\\\"%step%\\\", 1]\"]},{\"Description\":\"Set value to a variable then Store/Save variable(s) in a persistant storage. The storing of the variables must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetValueAndStore\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"dataSourceName\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Store/Save variable(s) in a persistant storage\",\"MethodName\":\"Store\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"dataSourceName\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"One or more variables to return. Variable can contain !, e.g. !callback=%callback%. When key is undefined, it is same as value, e.g. return %name% => then variables dictionary has key and value as name=%name%\",\"MethodName\":\"Return\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"OnCreateVariablesListener\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"keys\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.GoalToCallInfo\",\"Name\":\"goalName\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"waitForResponse\",\"DefaultValue\":true,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"delayWhenNotWaitingInMilliseconds\",\"DefaultValue\":50,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"OnChangeVariablesListener\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"keys\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.GoalToCallInfo\",\"Name\":\"goalName\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"notifyWhenCreated\",\"DefaultValue\":true,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"waitForResponse\",\"DefaultValue\":true,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"delayWhenNotWaitingInMilliseconds\",\"DefaultValue\":50,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"OnRemoveVariablesListener\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[System.String]\",\"Name\":\"keys\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.GoalToCallInfo\",\"Name\":\"goalName\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"waitForResponse\",\"DefaultValue\":true,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"delayWhenNotWaitingInMilliseconds\",\"DefaultValue\":50,\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"GetEnvironmentVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.String\"}},{\"MethodName\":\"LoadVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"}},{\"Description\":\"Set string variable. Developer might use single/double quote to indicate the string value, the wrapped quote should not be included in the value. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it\",\"MethodName\":\"SetStringVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"urlDecode\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"htmlDecode\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set json variable. Make sure value is valid json\",\"MethodName\":\"SetJsonObjectVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set default value of int/long variable. If value already exists it wont be set.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDefaultNumberVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"maxValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"minValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set date time variable. Example: set %lastUpdate% = \\\"2020-01-01 12:20\\\", or set %yesterday% = %now.AddDays(-1)%. When date/time being set, format it to ISO 8601.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDateTimeVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set int/long variable.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetNumberVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"maxValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int64]\",\"Name\":\"minValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set double variable.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDoubleVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Double\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Double]\",\"Name\":\"maxValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Double]\",\"Name\":\"minValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set multiple double variables.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDoubleVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Double]\",\"Name\":\"values\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set float variable.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetFloatVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Single]\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Single]\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set multiple float variables.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetFloatVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Single]\",\"Name\":\"values\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set bool variable width condition.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetBoolVariableWithCondition\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ConditionalModule.ConditionEvaluator+SimpleCondition\",\"Name\":\"simpleCondition\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Boolean]\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set bool variable.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetBoolVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Boolean]\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Boolean]\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set variable by calcuation, e.g. `set %total% = %quantity% * %price%`. Uses NCalc.Expression method, make sure it is valid NCalc expression. Capitalize any functions called like sqrt() into Sqrt()\",\"MethodName\":\"SetVariableWithCalculation\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"expression\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"decimalRound\",\"DefaultValue\":2,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.MidpointRounding]\",\"Name\":\"midpointRounding\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"Examples\":[\"set %total% = 5 * %item.amount%, round 4 => key=\\\"%total%\\\", expression=\\\"5 * %item.amount%, decimalRound=4\"]},{\"Description\":\"Set variable. Developer might use single/double quote to indicate the string value. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it\",\"MethodName\":\"SetVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"defaultValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"FullTypeName\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"\\r\\nConverts 2 dates to a number or timespan, such as days ago.\\r\\npattern=days|hours|minutes|seconds|milliseconds|nanoseconds|ticks|totaldays|totalhours|totalminutes|totalseconds|totalmilliseconds|totalnanoseconds\",\"MethodName\":\"GetTimeSpanRelated\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.DateTime\",\"Name\":\"fromDate\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.DateTime\",\"Name\":\"toDate\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"pattern\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"},\"Examples\":[\"set %days% = total days between %fromDate% and %toDate% => pattern=\\\"totaldays\\\"\"]},{\"Description\":\"Set multiple variables with possible default values used with variable(such as %request.query.*% and fix default. Number can be represented with _, e.g. 100_000. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it. onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Tuple`2[System.Object,System.Object]]\",\"Name\":\"keyValues\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set value on variables. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it.  onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetValuesOnVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"keyValues\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"Description\":\"Set default value on variables if not set, good for setting value if variable is empty. Number can be represented with _, e.g. 100_000. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it.  onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\\r\\nExample:\\r\\n`set default value %name% = %request.body.name%, %zip% = %request.body.zip%` => [{key=%name%, value=%request.body.zip%}, {key=%zip%, value=%request.body.zip%}]\\r\\n`set default value %target% = \\\"#body\\\" => {key=%target%, value=\\\"#body\\\"}\\r\\n\\r\\nBad (dont use for):\\r\\n`set default %page% = %request.query.page% ?? 1` => use:SetValueOnVariablesOrDefaultIfValueIsEmpty\\r\\n\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDefaultValueOnVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"keyValues\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}]},{\"MethodName\":\"SetVariableWithCondition\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"variableName\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"valueIfTrue\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"valueIfFalse\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"Description\":\"Set value on variables or a default value is value is empty. Number can be represented with _, e.g. 100_000. If value is json, make sure to format it as valid json, use double quote(\\\") by escaping it.  onlyIfValueIsSet can be define by user, null|\\\"null\\\"|\\\"empty\\\" or value a user defines. Be carefull, there is difference between null and \\\"null\\\", to be \\\"null\\\" is must be defined by user.\",\"MethodName\":\"SetValueOnVariablesOrDefaultIfValueIsEmpty\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.List`1[PLang.Modules.VariableModule.Program+VariableIfEmpty]\",\"Name\":\"variables\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"keyIsDynamic\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"onlyIfValueIsNot\",\"IsRequired\":false}],\"Examples\":[\"set %q% = %request.query.q%, or \\\"hello\\\" if empty => keyValues.key=\\\"%q%\\\", value=[\\\"%request.query.q%\\\", \\\"hello\\\"]\",\"set %q% = %request.query.page% ?? 1 => keyValues.key=\\\"%page%\\\", value=[\\\"%request.query.page%\\\", 1, \\\"System.Int64\\\"]\"]},{\"Description\":\"Append to variable. valueLocation=postfix|prefix seperatorLocation=end|start\",\"MethodName\":\"AppendToVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Char\",\"Name\":\"seperator\",\"DefaultValue\":\"\\n\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"valueLocation\",\"DefaultValue\":\"postfix\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"seperatorLocation\",\"DefaultValue\":\"end\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"shouldBeUnique\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"doNotLoadVariablesInValue\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"}},{\"MethodName\":\"GetVariable\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"}},{\"MethodName\":\"RemoveVariables\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String[]\",\"Name\":\"keys\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"Description\":\"Sets a value to %Settings.XXXX% variable\",\"MethodName\":\"SetSettingValue\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"Description\":\"Sets a value to %Settings.XXXX% variable but only if it is not set before\",\"MethodName\":\"SetDefaultSettingValue\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"value\",\"IsRequired\":true}]},{\"MethodName\":\"ConvertToBase64\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.String\"}},{\"Description\":\"Modifies a DateTime by applying one or more operations.\",\"MethodName\":\"ModifyDateTime\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.VariableModule.Program+ModifyDateTimeParameters\",\"Name\":\"p\",\"Description\":\"(see Type information in SupportingObjects)\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"},\"Examples\":[\"remove 1 day from %fromDate%, format 'yyyy-MM-dd' => Operations=[{Method='AddDays', Parameters=[-1]}], Format='yyyy-MM-dd'\",\"add 3 months to %startDate% => Operations=[{Method='AddMonths', Parameters=[3]}]\",\"subtract 2 hours from %timestamp% => Operations=[{Method='AddHours', Parameters=[-2]}]\",\"remove 26 hours from %now% => Operations=[{Method='AddHours', Parameters=[-26]}]\",\"set %date% as %now% but add one month then subtract 2 days => Operations=[{Method='AddMonths', Parameters=[1]}, {Method='AddDays', Parameters=[-2]}]\",\"take %startDate%, add 1 year, add 6 months, subtract 1 day => Operations=[{Method='AddYears', Parameters=[1]}, {Method='AddMonths', Parameters=[6]}, {Method='AddDays', Parameters=[-1]}]\",\"add %months% months then %days% days to %date%, format 'yyyy-MM-dd' => Operations=[{Method='AddMonths', Parameters=[%months%]}, {Method='AddDays', Parameters=[%days%]}], Format='yyyy-MM-dd'\"]},{\"MethodName\":\"TrimForLlm\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"obj\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"maxItemCount\",\"DefaultValue\":30,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Nullable`1[System.Int32]\",\"Name\":\"maxItemLength\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"groupOn\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"samplesPerGroup\",\"DefaultValue\":5,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"listLimit\",\"DefaultValue\":50,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Int32\",\"Name\":\"totalCharsLimit\",\"DefaultValue\":2000,\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Boolean\",\"Name\":\"formatJson\",\"DefaultValue\":false,\"IsRequired\":false}],\"ReturnValue\":{\"Type\":\"System.Object\"}},{\"MethodName\":\"GetSettings\",\"Parameters\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"key\",\"IsRequired\":true}]}],\"SupportingObjects\":[{\"Type\":\"PLang.Models.GoalToCallInfo\",\"Name\":\"goalName\",\"Description\":\"Name of goal and parameters that is called, e.g. in condition, loops, run goal. Keep Name as user defines it with path\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Name\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary`2[System.String,System.Object]\",\"Name\":\"Parameters\",\"Description\":\"Name of goal and parameters that is called, e.g. in condition, loops, run goal. Keep Name as user defines it with path\",\"IsRequired\":true}],\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ConditionalModule.ConditionEvaluator+SimpleCondition\",\"Name\":\"simpleCondition\",\"Description\":\"Logic: AND|OR. Operator: ==|!=|<|>|<=|>=|in|isEmpty|contains|startswith|endswith|indexOf\",\"TypeProperties\":[{\"Type\":\"PLang.Modules.ConditionalModule.ConditionEvaluator+ConditionKind\",\"Name\":\"Kind\",\"AvailableValues\":\"Simple|Compound\",\"IsRequired\":true},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"LeftValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Operator\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.Object\",\"Name\":\"RightValue\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"System.String\",\"Name\":\"Logic\",\"IsRequired\":false},{\"Type\":\"Sys